l5p:intro a l5p:DocSection ; l5p:order "s010" ; l5p:sid "intro" ;
    l5p:text "GENERATED by `ggen sync` from `.specify/pack-l5-promotion.ttl` -- edit the ontology, not this file.\n\nGoverning equation: `autosel = ggen(MaximalClosure(P_L5))`, where `P_L5 = { Promote(p) | p in P }` and `P` is every compatible ggen pack. Current per-dimension maturity (see `docs/packs/PACK_MATURITY_MODEL.md`) is an OBSERVATION, not a scope boundary -- every pack below is a promotion obligation until it reaches a terminal standing." .
l5p:completion a l5p:DocSection ; l5p:order "s090" ; l5p:sid "completion" ;
    l5p:text "## Completion condition\n\nThis program is complete only when every pack below has reached `Level5`, `Incompatible`, `Superseded`, or `RejectedWithProof` -- AND `autosel` is generated from the maximal lawful closure of the resulting Level5 population -- AND `autosel` can be completely deleted and regenerated without hand-authored product implementation. It is NOT complete when `autosel` compiles, when the 6 TCPS packs compose, or when this workflow merely exists." .
